    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Who Needs Musicians?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>F Gwynplaine Macintyre letter about Mar 25 article on use of computers to replace Broadway musicians says she cares only about performers on stage, not musicians (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>So the musicians' union is concerned that computer software might replace Broadway musicians? Boo hoo. This trend is sweet payback for the decades in which the union forced Broadway producers to hire ''walkers'': surplus musicians whose only job was to show up once a week for a paycheck. I pay to see and hear live actors, live singers and live dancers. Their accompaniment can be a jukebox, for all I care. If that knocks a few dollars off my overpriced ticket, I'll cry all the way to the box office.</p>
        <p>F. Gwynplaine MacIntyre  Manhattan</p>
      </block>
